<subSubSection id="C3326E8AFFF5C1037FE2FB49FA31FE58" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B973D01FFF5C1037FE2FB49FE9BF040" blockId="5.[136,1452,482,2057]" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF5C1037FE2FB49FDF3F344" box="[189,618,1274,1301]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">
Comment:— 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF5C1037E11FB48FDF3F344" box="[334,618,1274,1300]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Glossadelphus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="anomalus">Glossadelphus anomalus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
was described by Thériot in 1932, based on 
<specimenCount id="9D2EF688FFF5C1037B29FB48FA94F345" box="[1142,1293,1274,1301]" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" type="generic" typeStatus="syntypes">five syntypes</specimenCount>
(
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF5C1037A7EFB49FE6FF368" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">H.H. Chung B102, B105, B144, B194, B196</emphasis>
). Although morphological characters of this species are variable according to the environment conditions, the species is diagnosed by the following features: (1) filiform to foliose pseudoparaphyllia, (2) a large, inflated, hyaline, thin-walled cell at each base of leaves, (3) distinct proration at upper end of laminal cells, (4) asymmetrical ovate-lanceolate leaves, with crispate and serrate margins, and (5) obvious double costae. These characters do not fit the concept of 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF5C1037D45FA1CFD14F398" authorityName="Schimper" authorityYear="1851" box="[538,653,1454,1480]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Phyllodon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF5C1037D45FA1CFD14F398" box="[538,653,1454,1480]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">Phyllodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. For example, 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF5C1037C67FA1CFC32F398" authorityName="Schimper" authorityYear="1851" box="[824,939,1454,1480]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Phyllodon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF5C1037C67FA1CFC32F398" box="[824,939,1454,1480]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">Phyllodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has no inflated hyaline cells at laminal bases and filiform to foliose pseudoparaphyllia. While, they match well with the concept of 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF5C1037B17FA60FB63F3BC" authorityName="Mitten" authorityYear="1868" box="[1096,1274,1490,1516]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Ectropothecium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF5C1037B17FA60FB63F3BC" box="[1096,1274,1490,1516]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">Ectropothecium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as delimited by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB940F0FFF5C1037FD7FA45FF67F040" author="He, S." box="[136,254,1526,1553]" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" pagination="17 - 34" refId="ref8428" refString="He, S. (2019) Disentangling the taxonomy and morphology of Ectropothecium (Bryophyta: Hypnaceae s. l.) with comments on its generic relationships, and Neoptychophyllum, a new name for the genus Ptychophyllum. Bryophyte Diversity and Evolution 41 (1): 17 - 34. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / bde. 41.1.3" type="journal article" year="2019">He (2019)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B973D01FFF5C1037FE2F9A9FF52F02C" blockId="5.[136,1452,482,2057]" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">In all examined specimens, we have found that leaves of inclined branches are somewhat larger than those of prostrate branches. In addition, proration at upper end of laminal cells and crispate laminal margins are sometimes weak.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B973D01FFF5C1037FE2F934FE86F1CD" blockId="5.[136,1452,482,2057]" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF5C1037FE2F934FE4EF0F0" box="[189,471,1670,1696]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Glossadelphus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="anomalus">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF5C1037FE2F934FE4EF0F0" box="[189,471,1670,1696]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">Glossadelphus anomalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was once synonymized under 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF5C1037C6EF935FC5CF0F0" authorityName="M. Fleischer (1923:" authorityYear="1353" baseAuthorityName="Dozy &amp; Molkenboer" baseAuthorityYear="1844" box="[817,965,1671,1697]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Glossadelphus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="prostratus">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF5C1037C6EF935FC5CF0F0" box="[817,965,1671,1697]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">G. prostratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB940F0FFF5C1037CB0F934FB10F0F0" author="Tixier, P." box="[1007,1161,1670,1696]" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" pagination="319 - 356" refId="ref9667" refString="Tixier, P. (1988) Le genre Glossadelphus Fleisch. (Sematophyllaceae, Musci) et sa valeur. Nova Hedwigia 46: 319 - 356." type="journal article" year="1988">Tixier (1988)</bibRefCitation>
. After examining the 
<typeStatus id="549383A3FFF5C1037A24F935FA32F0F1" box="[1403,1451,1671,1697]" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">type</typeStatus>
specimens of both species, we conclude that 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF5C1037DCEF919FCBAF094" box="[657,803,1706,1733]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Glossadelphus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="anomalus">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF5C1037DCEF919FCBAF094" box="[657,803,1706,1733]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">G. anomalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not conspecific with 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF5C1037B63F919FB4AF094" authorityName="M. Fleischer (1923:" authorityYear="1353" baseAuthorityName="Dozy &amp; Molkenboer" baseAuthorityYear="1844" box="[1084,1235,1707,1733]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Glossadelphus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="prostratus">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF5C1037B63F919FB4AF094" box="[1084,1235,1707,1733]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">G. prostratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, because the latter has blunt leaf apices and distinctly contracted leaf bases. Therefore, we reinstate 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF5C1037B61F97DFB48F0B8" box="[1086,1233,1742,1769]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Glossadelphus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="anomalus">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF5C1037B61F97DFB48F0B8" box="[1086,1233,1742,1769]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">G. anomalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as an independent species, but transfer it to 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF5C1037EC3F940FDD7F15C" authorityName="Mitten" authorityYear="1868" box="[412,590,1778,1804]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Ectropothecium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF5C1037EC3F940FDD7F15C" box="[412,590,1778,1804]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">Ectropothecium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
here as, 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF5C1037DF2F940FBB7F15D" authority="(Ther.)" baseAuthorityName="Ther." box="[685,1070,1778,1805]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Ectropothecium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="anomalum">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF5C1037DF2F940FC42F15C" box="[685,987,1778,1804]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">Ectropothecium anomalum</emphasis>
(Thér.)
</taxonomicName>
Z.-Q. Yi &amp; Y. Jia. 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF5C1037BA5F940FF67F160" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Ectropothecium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="anomalum">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF5C1037BA5F940FF67F160" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">Ectropothecium anomalum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from all other Chinese 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF5C1037D09F8A4FCC6F160" box="[598,863,1814,1840]" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF5C1037D09F8A4FC91F160" box="[598,776,1814,1840]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">Ectropothecium</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
in its small leaves with crispate and serrate margins. It might be confused with 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF5C1037EE9F889FDDBF104" box="[438,578,1850,1876]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Ectropothecium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="zollingeri">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF5C1037EE9F889FDDBF104" box="[438,578,1850,1876]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">E. zollingeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in obvious double costae and prorate laminal cells, but differ from the latter in smaller plants, shorter branches (
<quantity id="4CD090E4FFF5C1037D42F8ECFDE5F129" box="[541,636,1886,1913]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="2.0">2–5 mm</quantity>
vs. 
<quantity id="4CD090E4FFF5C1037DF3F8ECFC85F129" box="[684,796,1886,1913]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" unit="mm" value="7.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="5.0">5–10 mm</quantity>
), and smaller leaves (0.8–0.1 × 
<quantity id="4CD090E4FFF5C1037BD8F8ECFA96F129" box="[1159,1295,1886,1913]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" unit="mm" value="0.35" valueMax="0.4" valueMin="0.3">0.3–0.4 mm</quantity>
vs. 1.0–1.4 × 
<quantity id="4CD090E4FFF5C1037FD7F830FE8AF1CD" box="[136,275,1922,1949]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" unit="mm" value="0.45" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.4">0.4–0.5 mm</quantity>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B973D01FFF5C1037FE2F814FA31FE58" blockId="5.[136,1452,482,2057]" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">
<bibRefCitation id="EFB940F0FFF5C1037FE2F814FEFBF190" author="Theriot, M. H. I. &amp; in Potier De La Varde, R. A. L." box="[189,354,1958,1984]" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" pagination="53 - 67" refId="ref9627" refString="Theriot, M. H. I. in Potier De La Varde, R. A. L. (1932) Recoltes bryologiques en Afrique Equatoriale Francaise. Annales de Cryptogamie Exotique 5: 53 - 67." type="journal article" year="1932">Thériot (1932)</bibRefCitation>
described that 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF5C1037D52F814FCBFF190" box="[525,806,1958,1984]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Glossadelphus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="anomalus">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF5C1037D52F814FCBFF190" box="[525,806,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">Glossadelphus anomalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has monocostate perichaetial leaves. Based on our study, the description on inner perichaetial leaves presented by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB940F0FFF5C1037C54F878FC29F1B4" author="Theriot, M. H. I. &amp; in Potier De La Varde, R. A. L." box="[779,944,1994,2020]" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" pagination="53 - 67" refId="ref9627" refString="Theriot, M. H. I. in Potier De La Varde, R. A. L. (1932) Recoltes bryologiques en Afrique Equatoriale Francaise. Annales de Cryptogamie Exotique 5: 53 - 67." type="journal article" year="1932">Thériot (1932)</bibRefCitation>
was revealed to be based on another species (
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF5C1037FCEF85CFE14FE59" box="[145,397,2030,2057]" class="Bryopsida" family="Leskeaceae" genus="Pseudoleskeopsis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF5C1037FCEF85CFECCFE58" box="[145,341,2030,2056]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">Pseudoleskeopsis</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF5C1037EC7F85CFD82FE59" box="[408,539,2030,2057]" class="Bryopsida" family="Leskeaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="family">Leskeaceae</taxonomicName>
) mixed with the specimens (
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF5C1037C02F85DFBB1FE58" box="[861,1064,2030,2056]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">H.H. Chung B144</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF5C1037B69F85CFBE8FE58" box="[1078,1137,2030,2056]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">B194</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF5C1037BF8F85CFB75FE58" box="[1191,1260,2030,2056]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">B196)</emphasis>
of 
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF5C1037A4EF85DFA31FE58" box="[1297,1448,2030,2057]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF5C1037A4EF85DFA3DFE58" box="[1297,1444,2030,2057]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Glossadelphus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="anomalus">G. anomalus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
